article.headline: Alcorn State 89, Prairie View 70
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Delvin Thompson had 16 points, Clif Douglass added 14 and Alcorn State ended its regular season with an 89-70 victory over Prairie View A&M on Saturday night. Juan Wyatt had 10 points and 10 rebounds and freshman Jarvis Williams finished with 10 points for Alcorn State (8-19, 8-10 Southwestern Athletic Conference), which won despite playing without forward Almaad Jackson, who was out with a back injury. The Braves outrebounded Prairie View 47-32 and had a season-high 29 assists. Oscar Thompson led Prairie View (5-24, 2-16) with 22 points.
